MBOMBELA – According to Hi-Tech Security operations manager for White River and Hazyview, Jchaan de Beer, the van security were coming out of a shop with a money trolley when they were ambused. “A trolley with money and a firearm was taken. So far we know, no shots were fired and nobody was injured.” ALSO READ: BREAKING NEWS: Three killed in accident on R40 near Hazyview He said the suspects fled the scene in a silver Toyota Fortuna with false registration number plates in the direction of Bushbuckridge.